===Phonosemantic interpretation===

[[w:Old_Chinese|Old_Chinese]] [[w:Old_Chinese_phonology#Initials|Initial]] {{IPAchar|/*-k/}} lends semantic value '''Frame'''. [[w:Old_Chinese_phonology#Vowels|Vowel]] {{IPAchar|/*-ua-/}} lends semantic value '''Curving/Round'''. [[w:Seal_script|Seal script style]] is　[[w:Chinese_character_classification#Phono-semantic_compound_characters|phono-semantic indicator]] [[又]] (the right hand/arm) + [[w:Radical_(Chinese_character)#Semantic_elements|semantic indicator]] an object → the right hand/arm (used in protecting). Source: [http://www.kanjinetworks.com/eng/kanji-dictionary/online-kanji-etymology-dictionary.cfm?kanji_id=KUAG14 Howell & Morimoto]

===Etymology===
右 is from the combination of the phonetic element [[又]], semantically a [[protecting]] [[right]] [[arm]], and [[口]], which here merely signifies an [[object]]. The [[right]] [[hand]] is traditionally the one used in [[protecting]] an [[object]] while carrying it.

